      <hedline>
        <hl1>GRANADA AND COMPASS TO MERGE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Alan Cowell</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cowell, Alan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>In an all-stock deal worth $8 billion, Granada Group and Compass Group agree to merge, allowing Granada to start spinning off its media unit this summer (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In an all-stock deal worth $8 billion, Granada Group and Compass Group have agreed to merge, allowing Granada to start spinning off its media unit this summer. Granada, Britain's biggest hotel owner, owns a third of the Independent Television Network and wants to separate its media arm so that it can pursue acquisitions. Compass is Britain's leading caterer.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell (NYT)</p>
      </block>
